                            <comment id="191072" author="dmiter" created="Thu, 6 Apr 2017 19:22:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was fixed in&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6401&quot; title=&quot;Untangle lustre userland and kernel headers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6401&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6401&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="191048" author="dmiter" created="Thu, 6 Apr 2017 16:44:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No. Originally it was for IEEL release. But I&apos;d like to backport the patch. So, I&apos;m happy if it not needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="191029" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 6 Apr 2017 15:13:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you seeing this on master? The patch&#160;9f19e2f1 (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6401&quot; title=&quot;Untangle lustre userland and kernel headers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6401&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6401&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lustre: make lustre_user.h compile in user space) for master removed libcfs headers and replaced them with proper kernel headers. Exposing libcfs/types.h to userspace is not the right fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="191018" author="gerrit" created="Thu, 6 Apr 2017 14:48:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Dmitry Eremin (dmitry.eremin@intel.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/26416&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/26416&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
